OL,3,CTwo thirds of parents support ban on
OL,4,Cchildren using social media
OL,6,F30% of parents also said there
OL,7,Fchildren were spending between 3 and 8
OL,8,Fhours a day on social media, while 43%
OL,9,Fsaid social media companies aren't
OL,10,Fdoing enough to protect children from
OL,11,Fharm online.
OL,13,FA ban has also been the subject of
OL,14,Fdebate in Westminster recently, after
OL,15,Fmore than 128,000 people signed a
OL,16,Fpetition calling for one to be
OL,17,Fintroduced.
OL,19,FOne school in South Gloucestershire
OL,20,Fhas already taken steps to drastically
OL,21,Freduce phone usage amongst its pupils.
